abstract: KINGSTON, N.Y., Sept 3. -- More harmony prevails among the Republicans of Ulster County this Fall thus far than has been known before in many years, but it is expected that when the County Convention is held the Cornell-Coykendall-Sharpe feud will again manifest itself. abstract: TRENTON, N.J., Sept. 20. -- The spirit of the citizens of Newark is beginning to assert itself all over the State. abstract: SAN FRANCISCO, Sept. 28. -- An Important budget of news arrived to-day from Shanghai, China. The riots continue in the interior and the northern provinces. At Shenpao a large crowd of bad characters surrounded a girls' school and began to throw stones. The servants of the school at first stoutly resisted, but, overpowered by superior numbers, they at last fled and the school premises were destroyed.

abstract: There is some excitement among the members of Congress Court of Foresters over the circumstances attending the burial of James McGrath of 111 Thorne Street. McGrath lived alone with his two-year-old child, and at his death Congress Court assumed charge of the funeral arrangements.
